&lt;p&gt;LIVERPOOL UNIVERSITY HOSPITALS NHS FOUNDATION TRUSTCONSULTANT IN RHEUMATOLOGY AND ACUTE MEDICINE (10 PAs)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated and enthusiastic colleague to join our progressive and dynamic team. This unique post combines 60% rheumatology and 40% acute medicine in AMU, promoting specialty in-reach to the acute medicine service. The role will involve working across the three hospital sites. There is no out of hours or on call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to be joining us in Liverpool as the merger of the Royal Liverpool and Broadgreen University Trust with Aintree University Hospital Trust creates one of the largest rheumatology departments in the UK and as we plan for the opening of the state of the art New Royal Hospital. The candidate will have an excellent opportunity to help to shape the new merged department and further develop the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate must have completed specialist training in Rheumatology and GIM (or be within 6 months of attaining specialist registration at the time of interview), hold MRCP (UK) or equivalent and have full GMC registration with a licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Kate NelsonJob titleConsultant RheumatologistAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opportunities this post offers can best be appreciated by visiting the department, we would be delighted to welcome interested candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
